<item>
            <title>[HBASE-7524] hbase-policy.xml is improperly set thus all rules in it can be by-passed</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HBASE-7524</link>
                <project id="12310753" key="HBASE">HBase</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This should be a code error.&lt;br/&gt;
In HBasePolicyProvider.java, hbase-policy.xml file was set as,&lt;br/&gt;
conf.set(&quot;hadoop.policy.file&quot;, &quot;hbase-policy.xml&quot;);&lt;br/&gt;
But in Hadoop ServiceAuthorizationManager.java, policy file was get as,&lt;br/&gt;
    String policyFile = &lt;br/&gt;
      System.getProperty(&quot;hadoop.policy.file&quot;, HADOOP_POLICY_FILE);&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The result is, the mentioned hbase-policy.xml file won&apos;t be used, and &lt;br/&gt;
default hadoop-policy.xml file can be used, which is unexpected.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
